<dl id="n42021a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42021a">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42021a"> 21(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> infallible God</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The priest of Rome is an automaton, tied to the feet of the Pope by an iron chain. He can move, go right or left, up or down; he can think and act, but only at the bidding of the infallible god of Rome. <small> Chiniquy, <a name="CPWC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CPWC"><cite title="source">The Priest The Woman and The Confessional</cite></a> (n.d.) 99</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
